{
  "id": "019d2d89-4114-7083-8b6b-020ecf3594b3",
  "content": "# Emerging Patterns in AI Agent Memory (Late 2025 → March 2026)\n\n## 1. Write-Time Intelligence Beats Retrieval-Time Intelligence\nThe strongest emerging consensus. Systems that front-load entity extraction, fact resolution, and graph construction at ingestion get fast, LLM-free retrieval. Zep does zero LLM calls at retrieval time. This consistently outperforms systems that do intelligence at query time.\n\n## 2. Active Forgetting is a Design Principle\nRedis Agent Memory Server: 5-stage lifecycle with 4 forgetting policies (age-based 90d, inactivity-based 30d, combined, budget-based top-N). Background compaction every 10 minutes. Mirrors neuroscience research on memory consolidation during sleep.\n\n## 3. Memory-as-a-Service vs Embedded (Market Bifurcation)\nCloud: Mem0 Cloud, Zep Cloud, Graphlit. Local-first: Redis Agent Memory, SuperLocalMemory, corvia. Converging toward self-hostable services with optional cloud acceleration. SuperLocalMemory V3 achieves 74.8% LoCoMo entirely offline.\n\n## 4. Multi-Channel Retrieval Fusion\nTop systems run parallel retrieval: semantic vector + BM25 keyword + graph traversal + temporal filtering, combined with cross-encoder reranking. Single-channel vector search is no longer competitive.\n\n## 5. Reflection and Self-Improvement Loops\nHottest research area. SAGE (self-evolving agents with forgetting curves), Hindsight CARA (configurable disposition: skepticism, literalism, empathy), MemRL (runtime reinforcement learning on episodic memory), A-MEM (Zettelkasten-style autonomous linking, NeurIPS 2025). Stanford HAI confirms agents that self-reflect perform measurably better in changing environments.\n\n## 6. MCP Memory Server Ecosystem Growing\n6+ MCP memory servers: Official MCP Memory, Basic Memory, ContextForge, Recallium, mcp-memory-service, agent-memory-mcp-server. Corvia differentiates via multi-agent coordination, graph reasoning, and health validation.\n\n## 7. Context Engineering > Prompt Engineering\nAnthropic (Sep 2025): \"Every token competes for attention. Agents forget because signal gets drowned by accumulation.\" Key strategies: selective context loading, progressive summarization, write-time intelligence, memory budgets. 65% of enterprise AI failures in 2025 attributed to context drift, not context exhaustion.",
